      "role": "user",
      "content": "but there's nothing to draw on. there is literally nothing left. even if i take a tiny step, there's no ground beneath me. it's just... it's just so heavy. it feels like the most logical thing is to just stop fighting it. doesn't it make sense that someone would just want to let go when everything is already gone?",
